Attention WB Marching Band Families:

We are excited to share today the performance schedule for our Warrior Marching Band. This Fall, our band will be attending four (4) Home Varsity football games as well as hosting two WB Band Nights. In addition to these six (6) events, our senior band members will be recognized, along with their peers participating in football and cheerleading, during the football game on September 19th at the P-O Stadium. Specific dates will be shared on a weekly basis along with athletic events. As with all of our programs and services, the plans are subject to change as dictated by COVID-19. Thank you.

Attention WB Athletic Families & Fans:

Please be advised that school districts were made aware around 2:00 p.m. of the revised guidance pertaining to spectators at athletic events. Due to the short notice, the District is maintaining our current "no spectator" guideline until we can take this evening to review the new guidance and adjust our procedures accordingly. While this may be good news for some of our athletic teams, it presents little to no relief for other teams. We will provide an update to all by tomorrow.

Thank you for your patience as we work through this new change.

post_text:
Attention Parents/Guardians of Incoming 5th Grade WB Students:

There will be an optional 5th-grade orientation opportunity on August 18th and August 19th from 4PM to 7:30PM. Due to current social distancing regulations limiting gatherings to 25 people or less, this orientation will be by appointment only. We will be scheduling 30-minute sessions each day. The following time slots will be available each day:

4-4:30 PM
4:30-5 PM
5-5:30 PM
5:30-6 PM
6-6:30 PM
6:30-7 PM
7-7:30 PM

Each time slot can accommodate up to 10 students. Each student may bring one parent/guardian. In order to reserve your time slot, Please email the middle school principal at mmitchell@westbranch.org. Once a particular time slot is filled with 10 students, that time slot will become unavailable.

In the event that the requested time slot is unavailable for both days, a suitable alternative will be provided.

Please be aware that masks are required for the parent/guardian and the child attending the orientation.

Thank you

High School Yearbooks will be distributed on Thursday, July 23rd from 10:00 - 1:00 pm outside of the HS office. MASKS ARE REQUIRED.

SENIOR ONLY PICK-UP 10:00 - 11:00 am: Class of 2020 can pick up their books and graduation pictures/videos from 10:00--11:00. There are 14 extra available yearbooks which are being offered to seniors first. Seniors who did not purchase a yearbook but would like to, can do so during this time frame.

GRADES 9-12 PICK-UP 11:00 - 1:00 pm: All HS students who purchased a yearbook can pick up their books during this time frame.

Students who owe money on their book will need to pay for the remaining balance before receiving their yearbook. Cash or check (WB YEARBOOK) will be accepted at pick-up.

ALTERNATIVE PICKUP: MONDAY, JULY 27th, 2:00 - 3:00 pm outside of the HS office.

A parent must be present to sign the COVID-19 participation waiver or players will not be permitted on the field. If you have any questions please call Kris Matson at (814)592-9978. Thank you!

The YMCA is organizing a food drive. WB soccer is going to help support this cause to reduce hunger in our community.

Team members and community members can drop off donations at the field behind Gethsemane church. Donations can be dropped off on July 2 and July 9 from 4:30 to 6:30. Players will be there to receive donations. Please wear a mask and maintain social distancing during drop off.

post_text:
Parents, we still have some ELIGIBLE PreK slots open. If you are interested, please call us today to discuss!

Cen Clear - West Branch Preschool Partnership
Student Recruitment
2020-2021

The West Branch Area School District and CenClear are pleased to announce that recruitment is underway and we are accepting applications for the 2020-2021 preschool program. Interested families will be scheduled for a formal screening prior to an enrollment offer.

Through this partnership, we will be able to service children in a number of program options:

• Full Day:
5 days per week / 2 home visits per year / 2 conferences per year

• Home-Based:
2 home visits per month / 2 group activities per month

Children must be 3 years of age or 4 years of age before September 1, 2020; Income eligibility and readiness screenings may be required for enrollment; transportation will be provided for select programs upon request.

Please contact the West Branch Area School District at 814-345-5616, extension 4000.

post_text: The District is aware of a recent student post that does not align to the principles and ideals of our educational organization. While the video was not created on or with school property, it nonetheless indirectly places the District in the midst of our current national situation. The District condemns the content of the video in the strongest of terms. The content in the video is harmful, racist, profoundly inappropriate, and antithetical to the mission and goal of the District to provide a safe and healthy educational environment free of any type of invidious discrimination or hateful invective. The District will continue to educate our students on issues of racism and appropriate activism in an effort to eliminate all forms of discrimination. The continued publication of the video by visitors to the page is likewise highly inappropriate and any posting of the video will be deemed an unauthorized misuse of our page. The District is taking the appropriate action to stop the further propagation of such harmful content.

post_text:
Mindful Moment: Happy Earth Day!

Take some time to appreciate our Earth today while practicing mindfulness. Let's get creative and mud paint!

Ingredients:
- Powder paint/Paint/Food coloring
- Dishwashing liquid
- Water
- Cardboard
- Paint brushes

Directions:
1. Place your mud in individual containers
2 Add a color source from the ingredient list
3. Add a squirt of dishwashing liquid (this helps the mud paint spread and helps remove the color from clothing!)
4. Mx it up with some water to reach the desired texture
5. Paint away!

Message from the School Nurse

Hello Parents and Students!

I hope you are all staying healthy and safe during this unprecedented COVID-19 global pandemic. The goal of this letter is to reach out to all of you with some helpful information. Please know I am available via email, bbriskar@westbranch.org, with any questions, concerns, or updates to your child’s health status. Please take care!

Caring for you children during COVID-19
Below is a link with a great deal of information for your children and the pandemic
https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/prepare/children.html

Talking to Elementary Children About COVID-19
https://www.pbs.org/parents/thrive/how-to-talk-to-your-kids-about-coronavirus#.Xn4E32KFvBg.email

COVID-19 Resources
Make sure to get your COVID-19 information from reliable resources: PA Department of Health and the CDC are the most reliable sources with regularly updated information.
https://www.health.pa.gov/topics/disease/coronavirus/Pages/Coronavirus.aspx
https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/index.html

GREAT job with last week's puzzle challenge!

This week's challenge idea came from Mrs. McGonigal and should be a fun one! The challenge is to take a "forced perspective" photo - this means you use the power of optical illusion to make an object or person look much smaller or larger than they actually are. See the examples here. Send Mrs. Porter your challenge pics by Friday, April 17th. Can't wait to see what you come up with!
Mrs. Porter

post_text:
Middle School Weekly Challenge:

Hello, Students & Staff!
Here we are in week 4 of staying home and I don't know about you guys, but I am really starting to miss everyone! Mr. MItchell, the middle school teachers and I spent some time last week thinking about ways that we could stay connected to each other while school is closed and decided to have a weekly "challenge" that our students, faculty and staff can all participate in. There will be a new challenge each week that school remains closed. The challenges are designed to remind us that We Are All In This Together!

PUZZLE CHALLENGE!!!

This week, your challenge is to complete a PUZZLE - ANY puzzle - 50 pieces, 1,000 pieces, or somewhere in between! You can work by yourself, with a sibling, or anyone else at home. Take a picture of yourself with your completed puzzle and email the picture to Mrs. Porter (jporter@westbranch.org) by 3:00 on Friday, April 10th. We'll post the pics on social media, email, etc so that we can all see each others' work.

Now, go find a puzzle and get started!

Again, while RVSPing isn't required, it means the world to us so we can make this as smooth as possible for everyone. Thank you all for being so patient with us during this difficult time for everyone. Much love!

post_text:
March 13, 2020

Dear West Branch Families and Staff,

Following a communication from the Department of Education this morning, we are aware that Governor Wolf has issued a declaration that all State Agencies (including School Districts) shall postpone or virtually host planned large meetings, conferences, trainings, or community events. Although we recognize that the information we have is subject to rapid change, we will be cancelling all large gatherings as well as out-of-district student-travel beginning today until further notice to be in compliance with this directive.

Please watch for re-scheduled dates to be established once we receive additional guidance. We will keep you updated on any future events/closings as information/guidance on the situation develops.

Sincerely,
Michelle Dutrow
District Superintendent

Reminder: If you have a packet out, they are due back to Kasi Woodring by February 21, 2020.

Cen Clear - West Branch Preschool Partnership
Student Recruitment
2020-2021

The West Branch Area School District and CenClear are pleased to announce that recruitment is underway and we are accepting applications for the 2020-2021 preschool program. Interested families will be scheduled for a formal screening prior to an enrollment offer.

Through this partnership, we will be able to service children in a number of program options:

• Full Day:
5 days per week / 2 home visits per year / 2 conferences per year

• Home-Based:
2 home visits per month / 2 group activities per month

Children must be 3 years of age or 4 years of age before September 1, 2020; Income eligibility and readiness screenings may be required for enrollment; transportation will be provided for select programs upon request.

Please contact the West Branch Area School District at 814-345-5616, extension 4000.

post_text: On Wednesday December 18, students from the Elementary went out into the community to distribute our Random Acts of Christmas Kindness items. Our 4th grade STK group and their advisors - Miss G and Mrs. Kramer, along with 8 golden kindness ticket winners and Mrs. McGonigal and Mrs. White visited preschools, post offices, banks, grocery store, library, Windy Hill and Long’s Bus Depot. Our students brought holiday cheer to people of all ages, and it was very much appreciated!

post_text:
West Branch High School Spirit Week:

Monday, December 16: Twas the Night Before Christmas
Reindeer? The Grinch? Snowmen? Deck yourself in comfy holiday-themed PJs.

Tuesday, December 17: Colors of the Season
Wear red, green or white.

Wednesday, December 18: Welcome to the North Pole
Dress as elves, reindeer, snowmen, Santa or Mrs. Claus

Thursday, December 19: Sparkle and Shine
Deck the halls with you! Add bows, garland and other decorations you would put on a tree or package

Friday, December 20: Sweater Day and Sock Day
Make those sweaters ugly or not! Wear a holiday themed sweater and socks!

Daily prize for one lucky participant each day and points for your grade in the contest to see who has the most spirit!!

Be sure to check in at lunch to register for your chance to win. Checking in at lunch is the ONLY WAY to get counted for your class.

WEST BRANCH MIDDLE SCHOOL
2019 Holiday SPIRIT Week!
********************************************
WBMS Students & Staff: Get in the holiday spirit by joining in with SPIRIT week! Grade levels will compete for the highest percentage of student participation for the week. The winning grade level will receive a special holiday treat on Friday afternoon, compliments of the School Climate Committee.

Monday, December 16—Winter Wonderland (wear blue & white)

Tuesday, December 17—Christmas Character Day

Wednesday, December 18—Baby, It’s Cold Outside! (wear sweaters and winter socks)

Thursday, December 19—Red & Green Everywhere! (dress in red & green from head to toe)

Friday, December 20—’Twas the Night Before Christmas…(wear your PJ’s to school)

* NOTE—School dress code still in effect! All Spirit Week attire must comply with the WBMS dress code.

Community Walking Program is Back!!

Beginning Monday, November 4, 2019 from 5-8 p.m. community members and family may walk at West Branch. Please sign-in on the sign-in sheet by the Middle School / High School Library doors. Please follow the map for the walking course. There will be additional maps and arrows posted along the course. The program runs Monday to Thursday from 5:00 p.m. to 8:00 p.m. until April 30. If school is not in session due to holidays or inclement weather, there will be no Walking Program that evening.

We hope to see you here! Thank you for your support!

post_text:
On Tuesday October 22nd, a group of 4th grade students from WB Elementary attended an Empowering the Bystanders training with other local school districts. This event is designed to give students training in bullying and harassment prevention, focus on safe and effective interventions in bullying incidents, explore a wide range of choices to use as bystanders intervening in bullying on behalf of their peers, and create a positive peer environment within their school.

Students/staff in photo 1 are:
Mrs. Kramer, Sadie Smeal, Chase Bumgarner, Kendra Wenner, Abby Causer, Alexis Condon, Ashley Causer, Cale McDowell, Aiden Evans, Ms. Graboski

post_text: On October 24, WB Elementary and Middle School in conjunction with the WB PTO hosted their annual safe trick or treating event. Families, community members, and local businesses donated close to 18,000 pieces of candy to help this event be a success. This event brings in almost 800 local children each year. In addition to trick or treating through the school, families are also offered free hayrides by local community members who donate their tractors and time to help provide this opportunity.

shared_text:
West Branch Area School District added 20 new photos.
October 2, 2019 at 7:54 AM ·

‘We May be small, but we are mighty.’ A quote that describes our small WB community perfectly! Many, many, MANY special friends near and far, came together to sponsor every one of our WB Elementary students with a Scholastic Book! What does this mean? Every student in PreK through 4th grade will receive a free book every month from September to May- that’s 9 FREE BOOKS! We can’t say THANK YOU enough to each individual person, each family, and businesses that sponsored a child, and in most cases more than one! You have made an impact in their literacy life and for that we THANK YOU!! ❤️💙
